{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"@interface","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"MLNPolygon","kind":"identifier"},{"text":" : ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"c:objc(cs)MLNMultiPoint","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMultiPoint","text":"MLNMultiPoint","kind":"typeIdentifier"}],"platforms":["iOS"],"languages":["occ"]}]},{"content":[{"text":"Overview","anchor":"overview","type":"heading","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"You can add polygon shapes to the map by adding them to an ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNShapeSource"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"object. Configure the appearance of an ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNShapeSource"},{"text":"’s or","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNVectorTileSource"},{"text":"’s polygons collectively using an ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNVectorTileSource"},{"text":" or","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNSymbolStyleLayer"},{"text":" object. To access a polygon’s attributes, use an","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolygonFeature"},{"text":" object.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Alternatively, you can add a polygon overlay directly to a map view using the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMapView\/addAnnotation:","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMapView\/addOverlay:","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" method. Configure"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"a polygon overlay’s appearance using"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMapViewDelegate\/mapView:strokeColorForShapeAnnotation:","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" and"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMapViewDelegate\/mapView:fillColorForPolygonAnnotation:","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The vertices are automatically connected in the order in which you provide","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"them. You should close the polygon by specifying the same","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CLLocationCoordinate2D"},{"text":" as the first and last vertices; otherwise, the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"polygon’s fill may not cover the area you expect it to. To avoid filling the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"space within the shape, give the polygon a transparent fill or use an","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolyline"},{"text":" object.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A polygon may have one or more interior polygons, or holes, that you specify as"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolygon","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" objects with the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"+polygonWithCoordinates:count:interiorPolygons:"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"method. For example, if a polygon represents a lake, it could exclude an island"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"within the lake using an interior polygon. Interior polygons may not themselves"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"have interior polygons. To represent a shape that includes a polygon within a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"hole or, more generally, to group multiple polygons together in one shape, use"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"an "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMultiPolygon","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMultiPolygon","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" object."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"To make the polygon straddle the antimeridian, specify some longitudes less","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"than −180 degrees or greater than 180 degrees.","type":"text"}]},{"text":"Related examples","anchor":"Related-examples","type":"heading","level":4},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"TODO: Add a polygon annotation, learn how to initialize an"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolygon"},{"type":"text","text":" object from an array of coordinates."}]}],"kind":"content"}],"kind":"symbol","identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"occ","url":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolygon"},"relationshipsSections":[{"type":"inheritsFrom","title":"Inherits From","kind":"relationships","identifiers":["doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMultiPoint"]},{"type":"inheritedBy","title":"Inherited By","kind":"relationshi